\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1-12. L. corniculatus} group. Perennial herbs usually with woody stock. Calyx-teeth usually more or less equal, but sometimes curved; corolla 8-18 mm, yellow, sometimes orange or red and yellow. Legume cylindrical, straight. Seeds many.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28  A widespread, variable group containing diploid and tetraploid species. It is sometimes treated as a single species with a number of subspecies and varieties. Recent work has shown that there are a number of relatively local diploid taxa throughout C. & S. Europe and Asia (in addition to {\b 1} and {\b 9}), together with more widespread tetraploids. The data available at the present are insufficient to produce a comprehensive account of the group, and it is likely that some of the species recognized here are heterogeneous, while others may not be distinct species.
