\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. L. tenuis} Waldst. & Kit. ex Willd.,{\i   Enum. Pl. Hort. Berol.} 797 (1809) ({\i  L. tenuifolius} (L.) Reichenb., non Burm. fil.). Stems 20-90 cm, glabrous or sparsely pubescent. Leaflets 5-15 × 1-4 mm, linear or linear-lanceolate. Heads 1- to 4(-6)-flowered. Calyx-teeth equal, usually shorter than tube; corolla 6-12 mm, yellow; wings obovate-oblong. Legume 15-30 × 2-2·5 mm. 2n = 12.{\i   Most of Europe except the north-east and extreme north.} Al Au Be Bl Br Bu Co Cr Cz Da Ga Ge Gr He Ho Hs Hu It Ju Lu Po Rm Rs (W, K, E) Sa Si Su Tu [Fe No].
