\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. L. stenodon} (Boiss. & Heldr.) Heldr.,{\i   Sched. Herb. Graec. Norm.} no. 1419 (1897) ({\i  L. orphanidis} Ujhelyi; incl.{\i   L. preslii} var.{\i   rostellatus} (Heldr.) Hayek). Stems up to 20 cm, procumbent or erect, glabrous or sparsely hairy. Leaflets 3-12 × 1·5-7 mm, elliptic-oblanceolate to obovate. Heads 2- to 5-flowered; peduncle 1-6 cm; pedicels 0·5-2 mm. Calyx-teeth unequal, longer than tube; corolla 8-17 mm. Legume 10-30 × 1·2-2 mm. •{\i   W. part of Balkan peninsula.} Al Gr Ju.
