\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. L. glareosus} Boiss. & Reuter,{\i   Pugillus} 36 (1852). Stems up to 20 cm, procumbent or ascending, sparsely to densely villous, or with dense, silvery, appressed hairs. Leaflets 2-10 × 1·5-5 mm, obovate or elliptic-obovate. Heads 1- to 6-flowered, calyx-teeth ± unequal, longer than tube, linear-triangular or linear with triangular base, the lateral and upper teeth curved; pedicels 0·5-1·5 mm. Calyx-teeth unequal, as long as or longer than tube; corolla 8-10 mm, usually reddish. Legume 15-25 × 2-2·5 mm. •{\i   Mountains of S. Spain, C. Portugal.} Hs Lu.
